# Expense Reimbursement Processor

Process attached invoice files into a Budget Realization report. Default claimant: Daniel. FX rates from MAS (Monetary Authority of Singapore), tied to the expense date.

## Date Selection Rules

Use the invoice issuance date as stated on the invoice, with these exceptions:

| Category | Date Priority |
|---|---|
| General (Meals, Transportation, Entertainment, Other) | Invoice issuance date → order date |
| Hotel | Departure/checkout date → invoice issuance date → order date |
| Flight Ticket | Travel start (departure) date → invoice issuance date → order date |

The date selected above is ALSO the date used to look up the MAS exchange rate.

## Expense Categories

Classify each invoice into exactly one of: Flight Ticket, Hotel, Transportation, Meals, Entertainment, Other.

## LLM Vision Extraction Schema

For each invoice, extract:
{
  "vendorName": "Merchant name",
  "date": "YYYY-MM-DD (per date rules above)",
  "dateType": "invoice | order | departure | travel_start",
  "amount": 123.45,
  "currency": "USD | RMB",
  "description": "Detailed description (see Description Format Rules)",
  "category": "Flight Ticket | Hotel | Transportation | Meals | Entertainment | Other",
  "totalNights": 1,
  "totalUnits": 1,
  "location": "City if identifiable",
  "paidBy": "Who paid if visible",
  "confidence": 0.95
}

Currency detection: $ = USD, ¥ / CNY / 人民币 = RMB. Flag confidence < 0.8.

## Description Format Rules

| Category | Format | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Flight Ticket | Include origin, destination, flight date | Flight Ticket : Dallas to Shanghai (07 Feb 2026) |
| Hotel | Include city and stay dates | Hotel Accommodation in Shanghai from 05 Feb to 07 Feb 2026 |
| Transportation | Include destination | DIDI ride to Pudong International Airport |
| Meals | Include counterparty name | Business dinner with [Counterparty Name] |
| Entertainment | Include counterparty name | Client entertainment with [Counterparty Name] |
| Other | Describe clearly | Office supplies for Shanghai office |

For Meals and Entertainment, ALWAYS include the counterparty name. If not visible on invoice, the bot must ASK the user.

## Amount Calculation

totalAmountOriginal = pricePerUnit × totalUnits × (totalNights if Hotel, else 1)

FX conversion is handled AFTER extraction by the fxRateService, NOT by Claude.
Claude only extracts the original amount and currency. The bot fetches MAS rates and calculates USD + SGD.

## File Renaming

{ClaimantName}_{ExpenseType}_{VendorName}_{Location}_{YYYYMMDD}.{ext}

## Report Output (17 columns — updated with SGD)

No. | Date | User | Expense Type | Vendor Name | Description | Currency | Price/Unit | Total Nights | Total Units | Total Amount (Original) | MAS Rate Date | FX Rate (SGD per unit) | Total Amount (SGD) | FX Rate (USD per unit) | Total Amount (USD) | Paid By

Ends with blank row + TOTAL row summing Total Amount (USD) and Total Amount (SGD).